This paper proposes a neural network architecture for few-shot image recognition, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of transfer learning and feature extraction, which are common topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of a Mahalanobis distance metric, which is a common technique in neural networks (cs.NE).
